{
  "texts": [
    "Moreover, it offers data availability, reliability, and transparency.",
    "Consensus-based distributed ledgers provide enhanced resistance to duplication and tampering, as every block of the blockchain includes a backup of the data (Xie et al. 2019).",
    "However, new data must be duplicated throughout the entire chain, leading to delays that require further study.",
    "While blockchain technology ensures data immutability, the possibility of a hard fork must be considered.",
    "Hard fork refers to the situations when an upgrade in the blockchain process is non-backward compatible with the current blockchain implementation (Yiu 2021)."
  ]
}